-- JPMorgan’s Bruno Iksil Leaving Bank, New York Times Reports
-- B y   D a n   K r a u t
-- 2012-05-16T18:16:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-16/jpmorgan-s-bruno-iksil-leaving-bank-new-york-times-reports.html
JPMorgan Chase & Co. (JPM) ’s Bruno Iksil is
leaving the bank after trades on credit derivatives at the unit
where he worked accumulated $2 billion in losses, the New York
Times reported citing unidentified traders.  Iksil is expected to be gone by the end of the year, the
newspaper said in an updated version of its story, citing people
with knowledge of the situation.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Dan Kraut in New York at 
 dkraut2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
